-- Mexico Inclusion In World Bond Index to Spur $16 Billion Inflows, RBC Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-28T04:20:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/mexico-inclusion-in-world-bond-index-to-spur-16-billion-inflows-rbc-says.html
Mexico is expected to be added to
the Citi World Government Bond Index on Oct. 1, a move that will
spur inflows of $16 billion into the country, or the amount of
foreign direct investment the nation gets in a typical year, RBC
Capital Markets said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
